  "title": "refactor(helper): replace getQueryParameter usage [PART-2]",
  "body": "The PR replaces the usage of the [`getQueryParameter`](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js/blob/develop/src/SearchParameters/index.js#L1552-L1560) function. This function rely on the previous structure of the `SearchParameters`. It does check if the given attribute exists on the state, if it doesn't it throws an error. This function will be removed from the [Helper](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js/pull/713). We've replace the call to a direct access to the state. You can verify that the tests pass for the changes with (note that the tests fail but it's only snapshots):\r\n\r\n```\r\nyarn test \\\r\nsrc/connectors/hierarchical-menu/__tests__/connectHierarchicalMenu-test.js \\\r\nsrc/connectors/hits-per-page/__tests__/connectHitsPerPage-test.js \\\r\nsrc/connectors/refinement-list/__tests__/connectRefinementList-test.js \\\r\nsrc/connectors/sort-by/__tests__/connectSortBy-test.js\r\n```\r\n\r\n> The CI does not pass, it's expected. It won't pass until the last PR of the stack.",
